---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import QuoteBlock from '../../../components/content/QuoteBlock.astro';
import BeforeAfterComparator from '../../../components/interactive/BeforeAfterComparator';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Nuevas Floras';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/nuevas-floras/nuevas-floras-01.jpg')).default;
const img2 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/nuevas-floras/nuevas-floras-02.jpg')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Nuevas Floras — Work"
  description="Nuevas Floras (2003–2007). Sculptural intervention on native trees. III Luis Caballero Prize. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 005</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2003–2007 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Sculptural intervention on native trees &nbsp;/&nbsp; Variable dimensions</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <img src={img1.src} alt="Nuevas Floras — Tree intervened with baroque carving, photographic series" loading="eager">
        <img src={img2.src} alt="Nuevas Floras — Detail of bark reclaiming the carving over the years" loading="lazy">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Nuevas Floras Versailles, 2017 ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Nuevas Floras Bristol ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Temporal comparator -->
      <hr class="rule--dashed" style="margin: var(--s4) 0;">
      <div style="margin-bottom: var(--s4);">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: var(--s3); padding-bottom: var(--s1); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 400; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">TEMPORAL COMPARATOR</h3>
          <span class="label">The tree responds to the intervention</span>
        </div>
        <BeforeAfterComparator client:visible beforeLabel="2003 — Intervention" afterLabel="2020 — The bark reclaims" title="Nuevas Floras — Temporal Transformation" />
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            In <em>Nuevas Floras</em> the artist intervenes on living native trees with carvings
            or prostheses of forms generally evocative of classical architecture and common elements
            in baroque church altars. Based on prior research, Escallon determined how to proceed
            without causing collateral damage, and the carved fragments were executed by experts.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            In a second moment, the arboreal beings respond to the action by interrupting the
            intervention, until making it almost imperceptible. Her practice creates a space where
            the 'wild' and the managed converge in time, where nature and culture are inextricably
            bound. The artist continues photographing these trees as they grow, making them active
            participants in the work.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The series presents as large-format chromogenic photographs (120 x 80 cm) taken
            immediately after completing the intervention. Since 2004, the project became a nomadic
            proposal responding to the specificities of culture-nature relationships at each site,
            with versions carried out in Colombia, the United Kingdom (Bristol), and France
            (Versailles and Chevreloup).
          </p>

          <QuoteBlock
            annotation="Curatorial text — Jose Roca"
            quote="Escallon's work aims to disturb the naturalness of that order. <em>Nuevas Floras</em> possesses two fundamental aspects: its nomadic character — because the idea from which it departs can be developed in other spaces — and the concept of temporality — because its duration is indefinite."
            cite="Jose Roca — Columna de Arena 53, August 2003"
          />

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            In 2003, Escallon won the First Prize of the III Luis Caballero Competition
            with this project, presented at the Galeria Santa Fe in Bogota. The jury,
            composed of curator Jose Roca among others, highlighted the way in which
            the work questions the boundaries between the natural and the cultural — a
            constant in the artist's trajectory.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The carvings made on the trees evoke forms from the Colombian colonial
            ornamental repertoire — Solomonic columns, volutes, elements of baroque
            altarpieces — creating a tension between the imposed cultural history
            and the organic response of the living being that absorbs and transforms it.
            Over the years, the bark reclaims the carvings, deforms them, integrates
            them, or makes them disappear.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">VERSIONS</h3>
          <ul style="margin-top: var(--s2); list-style: none;">
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <strong>Nuevas Floras Colombia</strong> — 2003. Native trees, Central Cordillera. Original version.
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <strong>Nuevas Floras do Sul</strong> — 2011. Brazil.
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <strong>Nuevas Floras Bristol</strong> — United Kingdom.
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0;">
              <strong>Nuevas Floras Versailles</strong> — 2017. Tuileries Garden (FIAC), Arboretum de Chevreloup, France.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Nuevas Floras</strong><br>
            2003–2007 (ongoing)<br><br>
            Sculptural intervention on living native trees.
            Wood carving, prostheses.<br>
            Documentation: chromogenic photograph.<br><br>
            120 x 80 cm (photographs)<br>
            Edition of 5<br>
            Variable dimensions (interventions)
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">AWARDS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            III Luis Caballero Prize — First prize<br>
            Galeria Santa Fe, Bogota, 2003
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">COLLECTIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Banco de la Republica, Bogota<br>
            ESCALA, University of Essex, UK<br>
            Seguros Bolivar Collection
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Encounters in the Dust Factory — MAMU, 2024<br>
            Nuevas Floras Versailles — FIAC/Tuileries, 2017<br>
            III Luis Caballero Prize — Galeria Santa Fe, 2003
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">TEXTS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <a href="/es/textos/jose-roca-columna-arena-53/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              Jose Roca, Columna de Arena 53 (2003) (ES)
            </a><br>
            <a href="/es/publicaciones/coleccion-seguros-bolivar/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              Seguros Bolivar Monograph (2018) (ES)
            </a>
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2003–). <em>Nuevas Floras</em>.
            Sculptural intervention. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/nuevas-floras/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  .work-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--s5) + 40px);
  }

  .work-page__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__header h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin: var(--s1) 0;
  }

  .work-page__meta {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ash);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .work-page__gallery {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s2);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__gallery img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .work-page__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--s5);
    margin-bottom: var(--s5);
  }

  .work-page__text h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ash);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .work-page__ficha h4 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--ash);
    margin-bottom: var(--s1);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .placeholder-img {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: var(--paper-dark);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--ash-light);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .work-page__body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
